summary: OK, a lot of people believe that a Nintendo Cinematic Universe is too complicated to actually work, but what about a Nintendo...
body:
OK, a lot of people believe that a Nintendo Cinematic Universe is too complicated to actually work, but what about a Nintendo Cinematic MULTIVERSE (or Smashverse as I call it)? Basically each movie (starting with Detective Pikachu) would take place in their own little universe and are only brought together by Master Hand and Crazy Hand or some other kind of villain and their universe hopping powers?

Thus, the heroes would have to work to save the whole MULTIVERSE instead of just one little lone universe. Not only that, but the movies in the Smashverse don’t necessarily have to be live action. Movies like Star Fox could be in full CGI and when the characters get together the CGI characters could mix with the live-action. Not to mention each of the movies could be in different genres (Detective Pikachu mystery, The Legend of Zelda fantasy adventure, F-Zero racing, Metroid sci-fi, Super Smash Bros. crossover)

summary:
Detective Pikachu: We did it!  We solved the mystery of R and apprehended the criminal!  Now the game is over!
Me: What about...
body:
Detective Pikachu: We did it!  We solved the mystery of R and apprehended the criminal!  Now the game is over!
Me: What about Harry Goodman?
DP: Who?
Me: Harry Goodman?  You know, Tim's father?  The character we've been searching for the whole game?  The whole reason we even got involved in the R case?
DP: ...shit, I knew we forgot something.
